In many states including Texas and Massachusetts, all convicted felons
are barred from holding auctioneer licenses.

In New Hampshire, which has in the past given the board of auctioneers
discretion in issuing licenses to felons, a proposed cleanup of laws
regarding auctioneers has led to controversy.

Details on the NH controversy can be found in the latest issue of Unravel
the Gavel. The online edition of Unravel the Gavel is found on the-forum

http://www.the-forum.com

The legislature breaks into two camps, those who feel that if the felon
hasn't stolen money, its okay to be an auctioneer and those who feel that
even a child molester or rapist should be refusedf a license.

How do you feel?

